observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to instruct the Municipal Treasurer
to:
• stop the use of improvised tickets and use the official accountable form 51 for the
collection of Environmental User’s Fee (EUF);
• stop the collection of fees by an unauthorized person;
• require the EUF Collector to accomplish the daily Report of Collections and
Deposits;
• require deposit of the collections intact and at least once a week or as soon as the
collections reach ₱5,000.00; and
• open a separate bank account intended for the EUF collections only.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct:

a. The Local Finance Committee to: adopt appropriate control measures to pay their tax/permit fees.

b. Local Finance Committee to adopt strategy in order to increase revenue/collections and monitor properly the availability of cash every month to ensure that all income due the Municipality be collected in full and assure continuous flow of funds and that the trust funds received be utilized only for the specific purpose for which it was created;

c. The Municipal Treasurer to prepare Daily Cash Position Report to serve as guide to him in certifying that funds are available to ensure that all disbursements have cash back up;

d. Municipal Budget Officer, Municipal Accountant, and Municipal Treasurer to exercise diligence, prudence and proper control in the disposition of the Municipality’s funds and limit expenditures within the total income realized and collected during the year to avoid incurrence of cash overdraft; and

e. The Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to explain why the Trust Fund was utilized and disbursed other than its intended purpose contrary to Section 309 (b) of RA 7160 and Section 84 of PD 1445, thus, resulted in the incurrence of cash overdraft amounting to ₱152,728.76.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

a. review the composition of the Solid Waste Management Board and, if necessary, reorganize it in accordance with the requirements provided under Section 12 of RA No. 9003 to ensure effective and efficient formulation and implementation of the Solid Waste Management Plan (SWMP);

b. designate a head of the Office of the MENRO on a concurrent basis to ensure that various Solid Waste concerns are immediately managed/resolved; 

c. instruct the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board (MSWMB) to compile the documents pertaining to the Solid Waste Management Plan (SWMP) of the Municipality, verify the status of its approval with the National Solid Waste Management Commission, and regularly convene to enable effective performance of its functions; 

d. encourage and support the establishment of Multi-Purpose Environment Cooperatives or Association to help promote the implementation of RA No. 9003; and 

e. thru the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board (MSWMB) require strict compliance of all Municipal Ordinances and monitor and require strict compliance of all Municipal Ordinances and impose penalties to those who will be caught violating the same.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct:

a. The Municipal Accountant to prepare the adjusting book entries to arrive corrected adjusted JEV and ensure that similar transactions will be adopted in the future;

b. The MDRRMO to implement the Capital Outlay projects as appropriated in the LDRRMF Investment Plan; 

c. The Municipal Accountant and concerned personnel to strictly adopt regulations on liquidation of cash advances ensuring the completeness of the liquidation supporting documents; and

d. The Municipal Accountant and concerned personnel submit the lacking disbursement vouchers to the audit team.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive review and strictly enforce the terms and conditions stated in the Memorandum of Agreement(MOA) specifically on the manner of collection of its share from diving fees and if warranted, issue a written demand to ensure timely receipt of shares on the dive passes collection on a weekly basis, in compliance with the MOA dated July 5, 2005;

Likewise, the Municipal Mayor instruct the:

the Municipal Accountant create special account in the general fund and the Municipal Treasurer with a SB Resolution open a new bank account in the nearest authorized government depository bank for the Conservation Trust Fund special account as prescribed in Ordinance No. 01 series of 2003;
the Municipal Accountant and other concerned municipal officials and employees submit the lacking documents to avoid suspension in audit and ensure the completeness of all supporting documents before processing payments.
the identified employees/laborers to refund the excess payment of wages amounting to ₱35,206.40
